CSS Background

The background properties control how the background of an element looks.

Example:

<div class="box">
    Hello World
</div>

We can change:

Background color
Background image
Image repetition
Image size
Image position
1. background-color

Sets the background color of an element.

Syntax
background-color: color;
Example
.box{
    width:200px;
    height:100px;
    background-color:lightblue;
}

Output

+----------------------+
|                      |
|     Hello World      |
|                      |
+----------------------+

You can use:

background-color:red;
background-color:#ff0000;
background-color:rgb(255,0,0);
background-color:rgba(255,0,0,0.5);
2. background-image

Adds an image as the background.

Syntax
background-image:url("image.jpg");
Example
.box{
    width:300px;
    height:200px;
    background-image:url("nature.jpg");
}

Output

+----------------------+
|      🌳🌳🌳🌳       |
|      🌳🌳🌳🌳       |
|      🌳🌳🌳🌳       |
+----------------------+

If the image is smaller than the element, it repeats by default.

