              🌄

You can also use pixel values.

background-position:20px 40px;

Meaning:

Move image 20px from the left
Move image 40px from the top
Complete Example
HTML
<div class="banner">
    Welcome
</div>
CSS
.banner{
    width:600px;
    height:300px;

    background-image:url("nature.jpg");
    background-repeat:no-repeat;
    background-size:cover;
    background-position:center;

    color:white;
    font-size:30px;
    text-align:center;
    line-height:300px;
}

Output

+------------------------------------+
|                                    |
|          Welcome                   |
|                                    |
+------------------------------------+

The image covers the whole banner, doesn't repeat, and stays centered.

Shorthand Property

Instead of writing multiple background properties separately:

.box{
    background-color:lightblue;
    background-image:url("bg.jpg");
    background-repeat:no-repeat;
    background-position:center;
    background-size:cover;
}

You can use the shorthand:

.box{
    background: lightblue url("bg.jpg") no-repeat center/cover;
}

Note: The / separates background-position (center) from background-size (cover).

Interview Questions
1. What is the default value of background-repeat?

Answer: repeat

2. What is the difference between cover and contain?
cover fills the entire element, even if part of the image is cropped.
contain displays the entire image without cropping, even if empty space remains.
3. What does background-position: center; do?

It places the background image in the center of the element.

4. How do you prevent a background image from repeating?
background-repeat: no-repeat;
5. Can an element have both a background color and a background image?

Yes. If the image doesn't fully cover the element or has transparent areas, the background color will be visible behind it.

Quick Summary
Property	Purpose	Example
background-color	Sets the background color	background-color: lightblue;
background-image	Adds a background image	background-image: url("bg.jpg");
background-repeat	Controls image repetition	no-repeat, repeat-x, repeat-y
background-size	Controls image size	cover, contain, 100px 100px
background-position	Controls image placement	center, top left, right bottom
